    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="231"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d231">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">London Embassy Files—710 Tripartite Conference
                    Berlin</note>
                <head>No. 231 <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_WJG2" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the British Foreign Secretary</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_EA1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Eden</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d231fn1">
                        <persName corresp="#p_HK1">Harriman</persName> conveyed the same information
                        to <persName corresp="#p_MVM1">Molotov</persName> in note No. 384 of July 8
                        (Moscow Embassy Files).</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-08">July 8,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. <persName corresp="#p_EA1">Eden</persName>
                    </hi>: In connection with the first item of the suggested list of topics for
                    discussion at the forthcoming meeting of the Heads of Government transmitted in
                    my letter of July 7, 1945,<note n="2" xml:id="d231fn2">See <ref
                            target="#d189fn1">document No. 189, footnote 1</ref>.</note> 1 have been
                    requested to communicate to you the proposal enclosed herewith<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d231fn3">Except for minor editorial variations, the text enclosed is
                        identical with the attachment to <ref target="#d228">document No.
                        228</ref>.</note> which the President plans to present to Prime Minister
                        <persName corresp="#p_CMWS1">Churchill</persName> and <persName
                        corresp="#p_SMIV2">Marshal Stalin</persName> at an early stage in their
                    forthcoming conversations.</p>
                <p>This document is being communicated in advance to the British and Soviet
                    Governments in the belief that they may wish to be giving the matter some
                    thought prior to the meeting.</p>
                <p>Sincerely,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WJG1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">John G. Winant</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
